---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import SectionHeader from '../components/SectionHeader.astro';
import Card from '../components/Card.astro';

// Page meta
const title = "Literature Review";
const description = "Summary of existing fake news detection methods and comparative analysis of different approaches.";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <section class="bg-neutral-50 py-20">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <SectionHeader 
        title="Literature Review"
        subtitle="Analyzing existing research and approaches to fake news detection"
      />
      
      <!-- Introduction -->
      <div class="mb-12 max-w-3xl">
        <p class="text-lg text-neutral-700">
          The field of fake news detection has evolved rapidly over the past decade, with various 
          computational approaches being developed to address this growing challenge. This literature 
          review examines key methods and their effectiveness in identifying misinformation.
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <!-- Summary of Existing Methods -->
      <div class="mb-16">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-primary-700 mb-6">Summary of Existing Methods</h3>
        
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
          <!-- Left Column: Methods -->
          <div class="space-y-6">
            <Card 
              title="Rule-Based Approaches" 
              borderColor="border-neutral-500"
              hoverEffect={false}
            >
              <p class="mb-3">
                Early fake news detection systems relied on handcrafted rules and linguistic patterns to identify potential misinformation.
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-sm text-neutral-600 ml-2 space-y-1">
                <li>Uses predefined lexical cues and linguistic patterns</li>
                <li>Often incorporates source credibility metrics</li>
                <li>Limited scalability and adaptability</li>
              </ul>
            </Card>
            
            <Card 
              title="Traditional Machine Learning" 
              borderColor="border-primary-500"
              hoverEffect={false}
            >
              <p class="mb-3">
                These approaches leverage statistical learning algorithms trained on labeled datasets of real and fake news articles.
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-sm text-neutral-600 ml-2 space-y-1">
                <li>Employs feature engineering (TF-IDF, n-grams)</li>
                <li>Common algorithms: SVM, Logistic Regression, Random Forest</li>
                <li>Better scalability than rule-based approaches</li>
              </ul>
            </Card>
            
            <Card 
              title="Deep Learning Methods" 
              borderColor="border-secondary-500"
              hoverEffect={false}
            >
              <p class="mb-3">
                Neural network-based approaches that can automatically learn hierarchical feature representations from text.
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-sm text-neutral-600 ml-2 space-y-1">
                <li>Includes CNNs, RNNs, LSTM, and transformer models</li>
                <li>Minimal feature engineering required</li>
                <li>Captures complex linguistic patterns</li>
                <li>Resource-intensive training process</li>
              </ul>
            </Card>
            
            <Card 
              title="Hybrid Approaches" 
              borderColor="border-primary-300"
              hoverEffect={false}
            >
              <p class="mb-3">
                Combines multiple techniques to leverage strengths of different methods.
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-sm text-neutral-600 ml-2 space-y-1">
                <li>Integrates content analysis with social context</li>
                <li>Combines linguistic features with source credibility</li>
                <li>May include user engagement patterns</li>
                <li>Increased complexity in implementation</li>
              </ul>
            </Card>
          </div>
          
          <!-- Right Column: Comparative Analysis -->
          <div>
            <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-sm overflow-hidden">
              <div class="bg-primary-700 text-white py-3 px-4">
                <h4 class="text-lg font-medium">Comparative Analysis</h4>
              </div>
              
              <div class="overflow-x-auto">
                <table class="min-w-full divide-y divide-neutral-200">
                  <thead class="bg-neutral-50">
                    <tr>
                      <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left text-xs font-medium text-neutral-500 uppercase tracking-wider">Method</th>
                      <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left text-xs font-medium text-neutral-500 uppercase tracking-wider">Strengths</th>
                      <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left text-xs font-medium text-neutral-500 uppercase tracking-wider">Weaknesses</th>
                    </tr>
                  </thead>
                  <tbody class="bg-white divide-y divide-neutral-200">
                    <tr>
                      <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-neutral-900">Rule-Based</td>
                      <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-neutral-900">Interpretable, No training required</td>
                      <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-neutral-900">Limited adaptability, Requires expert knowledge</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                      <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-neutral-900">Traditional ML</td>
                      <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-neutral-900">Efficient, Relatively transparent</td>
                      <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-neutral-900">Feature engineering needed, Limited contextual understanding</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                      <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-neutral-900">Deep Learning</td>
                      <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-neutral-900">Automatic feature learning</td>
                      <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-neutral-900">Black-box nature, Large training data required</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                      <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-neutral-900">Hybrid</td>
                      <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-neutral-900">Comprehensive analysis, Higher robustness</td>
                      <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-neutral-900">Complex implementation, Multiple data sources needed</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr class="bg-primary-50">
                      <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-primary-700">Our Approach</td>
                      <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-primary-700">Balanced efficiency, Clear interpretability</td>
                      <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-primary-700">Text-only analysis, Limited semantic understanding</td>
                    </tr>
                  </tbody>
                </table>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <!-- Justification of Our Approach -->
      <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-sm animate-fade-in">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-primary-700 mb-4">Justification of Our Approach</h3>
        
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
          <div class="bg-primary-50 p-6 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-primary-600">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-700 mb-3">Balanced Performance</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-700">
              Our TF-IDF + Logistic Regression approach strikes an optimal balance between computational 
              efficiency and classification performance while requiring significantly less computational 
              resources and training data compared to more complex models.
            </p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-primary-50 p-6 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-primary-600">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-700 mb-3">Interpretability</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-700">
              Unlike black-box deep learning models, our approach offers clear interpretability. The 
              TF-IDF feature importance scores allow us to identify specific terms and patterns that 
              contribute to the classification decision, enhancing transparency and trust.
            </p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-primary-50 p-6 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-primary-600">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-700 mb-3">Practical Implementation</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-700">
              The simplicity of our approach enables easier deployment and integration into existing 
              systems. It also provides a solid foundation that can be extended with additional 
              features or more sophisticated techniques in future iterations.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="mt-8 p-6 bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg">
          <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-3">Key Literature References</h4>
          <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm text-neutral-700">
            <li>
              <strong>Shu et al. (2017)</strong> - "Fake News Detection on Social Media: A Data Mining Perspective"
              <span class="block text-neutral-500 mt-1">Comprehensive survey of computational techniques for fake news detection.</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Conroy et al. (2015)</strong> - "Automatic Deception Detection: Methods for Finding Fake News"
              <span class="block text-neutral-500 mt-1">Analysis of linguistic cue approaches and machine learning methods.</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Pérez-Rosas et al. (2018)</strong> - "Automatic Detection of Fake News"
              <span class="block text-neutral-500 mt-1">Evaluation of linguistic features for fake news classification.</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Zhou et al. (2020)</strong> - "Fake News: Fundamental Theories, Detection Strategies and Challenges"
              <span class="block text-neutral-500 mt-1">Recent advancements and challenges in the field.</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>